Class TypeCoercer<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facebook.buck.rules.coercer.TypeCoercer<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - resulting type
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CollectionTypeCoercer, EitherTypeCoercer, FrameworkPathTypeCoercer, LeafTypeCoercer, MapTypeCoercer, NeededCoverageSpecTypeCoercer, OcamlSourceTypeCoercer, OptionalTypeCoercer, PairTypeCoercer, PatternMatchedCollectionTypeCoercer, SortedMapTypeCoercer, SourceListTypeCoercer, SourceWithFlagsListTypeCoercer, SourceWithFlagsTypeCoercer, TargetNodeTypeCoercer, VersionMatchedCollectionTypeCoercer

    public abstract class TypeCoercer<T>
extends Object
    Class defining an interpretation of some dynamically typed Java object as a specific class. Used to coerce JSON parser output from BUCK files into the proper type to populate Description rule args.

      • hasElementClass

        public abstract boolean hasElementClass(Class<?>... types)
        Returns whether the leaf nodes of this type coercer outputs value that is an instance of the given class or its subclasses. Does not match non-leaf nodes like Map or List.

      • traverse

        public abstract void traverse(T object,
                              TypeCoercer.Traversal traversal)
        Traverse an object guided by this TypeCoercer. #{link Traversal#traverse} function will be called once for the object. If the object is a collection or map, it will also recursively traverse all elements of the map.
